<HEADLINE>
<P>
 REALLY EXCITED BY MANILOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In response to Paul Grein's review "Could It Be Magic? Yes, If You're Barry 
Manilow" (Dec. 29), as I was the woman who was called up to the stage to sing 
"Can't Smile Without You" with Manilow, I feel compelled to respond to Grein's 
quotation of mine: 
</P>
<P>
 Yes, my answer to the question, "Do you know the words?" to "Can't Smile" was, 
indeed, "I did !" However, that was because I was excited and in total shock to 
be on stage with this talented, inspirational superstar Barry Manilow. I feared 
the words I knew so well might fly right out of my head; not that the song was 
so old I couldn't remember it, as Grein implied. 
</P>
<P>
 As a fan of Manilow, I would never insult or embarrass him. When he and I were 
singing together, he asked the audience to join in -- and they did, and that 
only proves that everyone knows the words to "Can't Smile." 
</P>
<P>
 CAROLE MECCA 
</P>
<P>
 Solvay, N.Y. 
</P>
