president of the merged company based in Los Angeles. In the 1970s, his family 
purchased a Southern California ranch and developed a vineyard on it, with Ream 
serving as founder, president and chief executive officer. He returned to the 
East Coast after his retirement in 1988. On Monday in Chester, N.J. 
