<P>
BABY ELEPHANT DIES OF APPARENT LONELINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A baby elephant, separated from a herd that had strayed off its fire-ravaged 
reserve and wreaked havoc in several towns, died in a zoo from infections and 
apparent loneliness. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried, but the little elephant is dead," A.K. Das, director of the 
Calcutta Zoo, said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 At least six people were trampled to death by the herd during its 10-day 
odyssey in early January that brought the herd as close as 60 miles to 
Calcutta, a city of 10 million people. 
</P>
<P>
 The herd has since returned to its forest home. 
