<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; OWNER SEEKS TO SELL NOREN'S MARKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The owner of Noren's Market, one of the few neighborhood grocery stores in 
Ventura, has announced that she is negotiating with buyers to take over her 
store. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're a dinosaur.We don't do enough business," said Peggy Carr, who has owned 
the store for more than three years. "Everyone goes to the big clubs." 
</P>
<P>
 Carr said most of her customers come in to purchase only a few things and do 
the bulk of their grocery shopping at supermarkets. The market offers fresh and 
dry goods, and its meat selection in particular has attracted a faithful group 
of customers. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr declined to give details of her negotiations with two potential buyers 
but said the sale may be closed as quickly as next week. 
</P>
<P>
 She said she has been losing money on the store and has been trying to sell 
the 39-year-old market on Telegraph Road for six months. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr said she did not know what would happen to her store after she sold it. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're grocery-store people, so I'm sure it will continue to be a grocery 
store," she said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
