<TEXT>
<P>
 An 88-year-old Oxnard woman who died after crashing her car into a parked 
vehicle was identified as Gladys Elfrink, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Elfrink had just stopped by her doctor's office Thursday to make an 
appointment when she suddenly swerved into a parked car in the 900 block of 
West Fifth Street.When rescue workers arrived, Elfrink was unconscious inside 
her car but had no visible injuries. 
</P>
