<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; TRIAL ORDERED IN MOLESTATION CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old Moorpark man was ordered Friday to stand trial on charges that 
he molested a 12-year-old girl after kidnaping her as she walked home from 
Chaparral Middle School in November. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Public Defender Todd W. Howeth, who represents defendant Roberto 
Magdaleno, said his client will be arraigned Jan. 28 in Ventura County Superior 
Court.Magdaleno, who is charged with five counts of child molestation, has 
pleaded innocent. 
</P>
<P>
 Howeth said the girl accused Magdaleno of taking her to an unoccupied home and 
attacking her on Nov. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 The defendant was arrested several hours after the girl reported the incident. 
An earlier preliminary hearing was postponed after prosecutors refused to put 
the girl on the witness stand to testify against Magdaleno. 
</P>
<P>
 Under state law, victim testimony is not required at preliminary hearings, 
Howeth said. Victims are required to testify only at trial. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors eventually agreed to let the public defender question the girl out 
of court, but the victim still refused to talk to him, Howeth said. Friday's 
hearing was held without her testimony. 
</P>
<P>
 "The law is designed to protect victims of crime," Howeth said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Rebecca Day, who is prosecuting the case, could not be 
reached Friday. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
