<HEADLINE>
<P>
RADAR WEATHER SYSTEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a Ventura County resident, I am interested in the placement of a radar 
weather tracking station on Sulpher Mountain. 
</P>
<P>
 Do we really need such as system? The U.S. government has spent billions of 
our dollars creating a weather satellite tracking system for the United 
States.Why, now, the change to a microwave system that creates hazardous 
radiation over a broad area? Why establish 115 such weather stations throughout 
the United States? Is there something here that our government is not telling 
us? I would like to know the strength, intensity, and distance that the station 
will send the microwaves. 
</P>
<P>
 Any variation in the intensity and strength in the microwaves will affect the 
human immune system and lead to a host of diseases. Studies have been conducted 
in Switzerland on the effects of microwave radiation. The results indicate a 
change in the blood leading to conditions that cause cancer. 
</P>
<P>
 Could it be that these radar weather tracking stations are designed for 
something else? 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD B. TUDOR 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Paula 
</P>
</TEXT>
