<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRASH TRUCK ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re: Dec. 29 article about trash truck driver injury in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 On behalf of my family, our drivers and other employees, I wish to thank the 
people who came to the aid of our driver, Adrian Ochoa.He was seriously injured 
on Dec. 28 when a hydraulic arm on the trash truck he was operating crushed him 
against the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 Without the fast action of Doris Hackett, the first neighbor who called 911, 
and the quick response of the Ventura Fire Department and Pruner Ambulance 
Service, this accident could have been fatal to our driver. 
</P>
<P>
 The nurses and doctors at Ventura County Medical Center are also to be 
commended. We as a community can be very proud of how accidents are responded 
to, and again, our heartfelt thank you to all who helped save Mr. Ochoa's life. 
</P>
<P>
 JIM HARRISON 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Harrison is vice president of E. J. Harrison & Sons, Inc.  
