<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Industrial Production Rises to 5-Year High: Output at the nation's factories, 
mines and utilities rose 4.2% last year, as measured by the Federal Reserve's 
industrial production index.That was the strongest increase since 1988 and 
followed a 2.3% rise in 1992 and a drop of 1.8% in 1991, a recession year. 
Production increased during each of the final seven months of the year, rising 
0.7% in December and 0.9% in November, which was the largest gain in a year. In 
December, production at factories rose 0.7%; at mines and oil fields, 0.5%; and 
at utilities, 1%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
