</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Northrop Gets More B-2 Funds: The Air Force said it awarded an additional 
$4.41 billion to the Los Angeles-based aerospace concern for continued work on 
the nation's final five B-2 stealth bombers.Production of the bat-wing aircraft 
is expected to be completed in early 1998. Northrop is building a total of 20 
B-2 bombers for the Air Force at a cost of $44 billion. The first operational 
B-2 was delivered to the Air Force last month. 
</P>
