<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; ACTING FIRE CHIEF IS APPOINTED NEW HEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT BARKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vincent F. Bonacker, 43, was appointed fire chief this week by City Manager 
George Tindall. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonacker has been acting fire chief since Sept. 1, when Lon Cahill retired.He 
joined the department in 1977 as a firefighter / paramedic after starting his 
fire service career three years earlier with the California Division of 
Forestry. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonacker emerged as the top candidate for the job from among 50 candidates who 
were recruited throughout the state, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy City Manager Mike Fenderson, who served on an oral board that 
interviewed candidates, said Friday that Bonacker "is extremely knowledgeable 
and has performed every function in the Fire Department." 
</P>
<P>
 A resident of Irvine, Bonacker has a bachelor's degree in public 
administration from Cal State Long Beach and is now pursuing a master's degree 
there. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council is expected to establish his salary Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonacker is married and has three daughters. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fire Department has seven stations and about 100 employees. ROBERT BARKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
