ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; LAGUNA CANYON WALK PLANNED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE EARNEST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The James Dilley Greenbelt Preserve in Laguna Canyon will be open for hiking 
and nature walks from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 The wilderness area is to be open on the third Saturday of each month through 
June.Walkers can follow a 1.5-mile nature trail or take a 2.5-mile stroll to 
see the county's largest natural lake. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, guided tours into the Laguna-Laurel Ecological Preserve, which 
was burned in the October fire and is now sprouting new vegetation, will begin 
Jan. 22. For reservations, call the Laguna Coast Wilderness Park at (714) 
854-7108. There are no public facilities in the wilderness areas. Dogs and 
bicycles are not allowed. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dilley Preserve, formerly called Sycamore Hills, is on the east side of 
Laguna Canyon Road, three-fourths of a mile north of El Toro Road. LESLIE 
EARNEST 
