<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; DRIVE-BY SHOOTING SUSPECT IS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An alleged gang member from Orange has been arrested in connection with a 
drive-by shooting that occurred on the San Diego Freeway last November, police 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jacob Morante, 21, is accused of pulling alongside an unidentified 24-year-old 
Huntington Beach man on the southbound lanes of the freeway near Harbor 
Boulevard, exchanging glances with the motorist, then firing a shot, said 
police spokesman George Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, who was not injured, heard the shot, looked over and saw the 
driver of the other car holding a small handgun, Wilson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He pulled over to inspect his car and found one bullet hole in the passenger 
door a couple of inches below the window," Wilson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was able to get a description of the suspect's car and a license 
plate number, which eventually led Costa Mesa police to Morante, who was 
arrested at his home late Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives searched Morante's home and found a loaded sawed-off shotgun and a 
small-caliber semiautomatic handgun, Wilson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morante is being held at Costa Mesa city jail on suspicion of assault with a 
deadly weapon, unlawful discharge of a weapon and possession of a dangerous 
weapon. His bail has been set at $25,000. GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
