<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monday is Martin Luther King Jr. Day. The following will be closed in 
observance of the holiday: 
</P>
<P>
 * City, county, state and federal offices, except the city offices of Buena 
Park, Costa Mesa, Cypress, Dana Point, Fountain Valley, Fullerton, Garden 
Grove, La Habra, La Palma, Laguna Beach, Laguna Niguel, Newport Beach, Orange, 
San Juan Capistrano, Stanton, Tustin, Villa Park, Westminster, Yorba Linda. 
</P>
<P>
 * Schools, including colleges and universities except Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 * County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
 * City and county libraries except Orange and Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: There will be no mail pickup or delivery, but mail dropped at a post 
office will be posted. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trash: Trash collection agencies will maintain regular pickup schedules. 
</P>
<P>
 * Buses: Orange County Transportation Authority buses will run on regular 
schedule.  
</P>
<P>
 * Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
during regular hours. 
</P>
