<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; DESIGN REVIEW BOARD APPLICANTS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is accepting applications from residents for two vacant positions on 
the Design Review Board, a five-member panel that studies the design of new 
projects that will have a major impact on the aesthetics of the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the Planning Division office on the third floor 
of Civic Center, 2000 Main St. They must be returned by Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants should have a background in development, architectural and 
structural design. 
</P>
<P>
 The Design Review Board makes final decisions on the design of some projects 
and makes recommendations to the Planning Commission and City Council on 
others. 
</P>
<P>
 City Councilman Victor Leipzig and Planning Commissioner Philip Inglee also 
serve on the Design Review Board. 
</P>
