<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS SIGN GRAHE, ARE NEAR A DEAL WITH EX-RANGER LEFT-HANDER PATTERSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 They are still not sure how they will use him, but the Angels signed reliever 
Joe Grahe to a one-year contract worth $925,000 Friday, avoiding arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels also have agreed in principal on a one-year contract with 
free-agent left-hander Bob Patterson.Patterson was 2-4 with a 4.78 earned-run 
average last season with Texas. 
</P>
<P>
 Grahe, who is eligible to earn $110,000 in incentives, probably will be part 
of the bullpen-by-committee arrangement. But if the Angels sign free agent 
Gregg Olson, Grahe would become a candidate for the fifth starter's job. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have no problems with however they want to use me," said Grahe, who was 4-1 
with 11 saves and a 2.86 ERA last season. "Really, either way will be fine." 
</P>
<P>
 Grahe, who sat out five weeks during the season because of tendinitis in his 
right rotator cuff, said he has been throwing without pain since the holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels also signed minor league reliever Ron Watson. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
