<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUNSET LEAGUE; OCEAN VIEW ENDS OILERS' STREAK AT 22 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER BARZILAI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After trailing most of the game Friday, the Ocean View boys' basketball team 
upset visiting Huntington Beach, 51-47, ending the Oilers' Sunset League 
winning streak at 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Carney's layup gave Ocean View (9-8, 4-1 in league) its first lead, 
44-42, with just over two minutes left in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a crazy game," Ocean View Coach Jim Harris said. "(Huntington Beach) 
has had a great stretch. I remember when we had a streak of 27 wins, and it is 
really something special." 
</P>
<P>
 With 30 seconds left in the fourth quarter, Matt Malmquist brought the Oilers 
to within 48-47, but Carney converted one free throw and Tim Walsh hit two to 
give the Seahawks the four-point lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are a very good free-throw-shooting team," Harris said. "(Huntington 
Beach) did everything right. They fouled people at the right time and just 
played real well. We were just able to get some transition buckets." 
</P>
<P>
 The Oilers (10-7, 4-1 in league) took an 18-8 lead, but Ocean View closed to 
within one at halftime, 25-24, on a last-second, 10-foot shot by Kevin Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach opened the third quarter with an 11-2 run, but Carney 
followed by scoring eight of Ocean View's next 12 points to cut the lead. 
Carney finished with a game-high 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
 "Mike Carney has shown a lot of heart," Harris said. "He carried us in the 
first half and then got some big buckets late in the game." 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach's Tony Gonzalez, who is averaging 24.7 points, finished with 
19 points after scoring 10 in the first quarter. He also had 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "Kevin Johnson did a great job on him at the end of the game," Harris said. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson finished with 12 points and Dan McDonald had 10 for Ocean View, while 
Malmquist finished with 14 points for Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 62, Westminster 42 -- Kristian Vallas scored 13 points and Mark Seaton 
added 10 and 11 rebounds for host Servite (11-5, 4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 64, Marina 59 -- Cesar Diaz scored 18 points for Santa Ana (2-10, 
1-4). Andy Nieto scored 19 points for host Marina (7-10, 1-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Edison-Fountain Valley -- Game was postponed because no officials showed up. 
The game will be rescheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
