<P>
LOCAL NOTES; SAN CLEMENTE'S KLAASEN COMMITS TO OREGON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Clemente linebacker Ryan Klaasen has orally committed to Oregon, Triton 
Coach Mark McElroy said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Klaasen, a two-year starter, was a Times' first-team All-Orange County 
selection this season.He was twice named to the All-South Coast League team. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Olson, a junior setter on the Irvine Valley volleyball team, has 
transferred to George Mason and will play this spring, the university 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Olson graduated in 1991 from Capistrano Valley, which won two league titles 
during his three varsity seasons. As a senior he was voted South Coast League 
MVP and participated in the Orange County All-Star game. 
</P>
<P>
 He was a two-year starter at Irvine Valley, where he averaged 14 assists and 1 
1/2 digs in 55 games. Olson was a first-team all-conference selection last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Harrison has been named the baseball coach at Western. Harrison coached 
the Pioneer freshman team to an undefeated record last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the El Toro water polo team, the Southern Section Division I 
champions, will be among those honored Sunday at the fifth CIF/Southern Section 
Water Polo Awards Banquet at the Sequoia Club in Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
 All-section players and members from the title runners-up teams: Corona del 
Mar, Sunny Hills, Costa Mesa and Los Amigos will also be recognized. Steve 
Heaston, coach at California, will be guest speaker. 
</P>
