<HEADLINE>
<P>
INJURED GOALKEEPER OUT FOR REST OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley goalkeeper Jason Felix, knocked unconscious Wednesday during 
a game against Mission Viejo, has been released from Mission Regional Community 
Hospital.Felix's father, Ray, said his son has a bruised spinal cord and will 
have to wear a neck brace for six weeks. He will be out the rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Ray Felix said Jason missed Capistrano Valley's first league game because of a 
broken nose suffered Jan. 7 during a dispute on campus. "He was blindsided by 
some kid and he had to miss the game that day because he was in emergency 
getting his nose fixed," Felix said. 
</P>
<P>
 Felix then played 10 minutes in Wednesday's game before being injured. DAVE 
McKIBBEN 
</P>
