<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; RANCHO ALAMITOS BEATS KENNEDY DESPITE FRANK'S INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos roared to an 11-1 lead before host Kennedy could get off a 
shot, but Vaquero Coach Peter Pyle looked worried. 
</P>
<P>
 Sitting on the bench was forward Michelle Frank, the team's second-leading 
scorer, who was hobbling after injuring her ankle only 49 seconds into the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank could not even join the team in the locker room at halftime, but the 
injury was noticeably improved by the end of the game which Rancho Alamitos 
won, 60-45, to improve its Garden Grove League winning streak to 42. 
</P>
<P>
 "She might have been more scared than anything else," Pyle said. "She felt 
that she could come back in the fourth quarter. We'll know for sure how serious 
it is tomorrow (Saturday)." 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy pulled it to 42-38 with 6:10 left in the game, but Rancho Alamitos 
survived. Jamie Franklin bounced a pass to Sally Vasquez for an easy layup and 
Detra Vickers followed with a basket and Akilah Rodgers connected on a 
three-point field goal to put the game out of reach, 49-38. 
</P>
<P>
 Janet Neuman opened the game with a three-point field goal on Rancho Alamitos' 
first possession and Rodgers followed with a field goal for a 5-0 lead before 
Frank was hurt. Rancho Alamitos built up a 17-7 lead after the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodgers, with a pair of three-pointers in the fourth quarter, paced Rancho 
Alamitos with 26 points. Karin Kitagawa had 14 and Leslie Prochasha added 12 
for the Irish. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos used a strong defense, forcing 16 first-half turnovers to take 
a 29-21 lead. But the Irish bounced back to 31-27 in the third quarter. MIKE 
WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
