<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; FULLERTON WINS A CLOSE GAME AGAINST RIVERSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton, the hard-luck men's basketball team in the first week of Orange 
Empire Conference play, won its second consecutive close game, beating 
Riverside, 77-74, Friday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton lost one-point decisions to Saddleback and Irvine Valley in its 
first two conference games before beating Orange Coast, 85-82, Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss dropped Riverside (17-5, 3-1) into a three-way tie with Rancho 
Santiago and Saddleback for first place. 
</P>
<P>
 Tyrone Merriweather had a team-high 23 points and Tamar Ross added 15 for 
Fullerton (17-6, 2-2).  
</P>
<P>
 Darryle Flicking of Riverside, who was averaging 33 points, was held to 11. 
The Tigers' Ronald Kenan had a game-high 36. 
</P>
<P>
 In other men's conference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 96, Irvine Valley 89 -- Marlon Watson had a key three-pointer 
with 2 minutes 54 seconds left to give host Rancho Santiago an 88-83 lead. 
Irvine Valley never got closer than four points the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean Amos and Matt Kordik each had 24 points for Rancho Santiago (15-6, 3-1). 
Arturo Clemente had 22 and Damon Sims 18 for Irvine Valley (14-8, 2-2), which 
has lost two in row. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 82, Cypress 61 -- Tes Whitlock had 25 points and seven assists for 
host Saddleback (13-6, 3-1). Antoine Jefferson added 12 points and 14 rebounds 
for the Gauchos. Adam Baker and Jeff Cummins had 12 points each for Cypress 
(10-13, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 96, Orange Coast 89 -- Host Golden West used a 12-2 run late in 
the first half and led, 53-46, at the half. The Rustlers then used a 13-3 run 
to go up, 82-66, with 5:33 left. Gerald Rhoden had a game-high 34 for Golden 
West (8-12, 1-3). Derek Roche had seven three-pointers and finished with 26 
points for Orange Coast (11-8, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference women's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 79, Orange Coast 71 (OT) -- Visiting Golden West (22-3, 3-0), the 
second-ranked team in the state, outscored OCC, 13-5, in overtime. Julie 
Murdent had 24 points for Golden West. America Robledo had 18 points and LeAnn 
Kazmer had 16 points and 17 rebounds for Orange Coast (13-9, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 49, Riverside 46 -- Nikki Kubota made four of four free-throw 
attempts in the final 38 seconds for visiting Fullerton (14-10, 2-1). Nikki 
Clark had 17 points for Fullerton. Riverside is 18-7, 1-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 67, Saddleback 43 -- Center Sara Works scored 22 points and Yolanda 
Hearvey added 16 to lead Cypress (18-5, 3-1). 
</P>
