<P>
 Stock price -- A story Dec. 18 about Reynolds Kendrick & Stratton, a Beverly 
Hills stock brokerage, did not fully state the details of trading in Hariston 
Corp., a Canadian company in which Reynolds Kendrick is a market-maker. As 
reported, Hariston shares, which closed at $11 on Dec. 17, traded as low as 62 
cents in 1992. But taking into account a later reverse 5-for-1 stock split, the 
low should have been reported as $3.10 a share. 
</P>
