 Nuclear waste -- A story on nuclear waste in Friday's editions of The Times 
inaccurately reported the half-life of plutonium.The correct number is 24,119 
years. Half-life is the time in which a radioactive substance loses half its 
radioactivity. Generally, such a substance remains radioactive for at least 10 
times its half-life. 
