<TEXT>
<P>
 13,000 Forgo Prudential Settlement: On the eve of today's deadline, more than 
13,000 investors have chosen not to participate in a revised settlement of a 
class-action lawsuit over Prudential Securities' troubled oil and gas 
partnerships.That is about 1,000 more investors than opted out of a much 
smaller settlement nearly a year ago. The first offer -- of $37 million in cash 
-- was derailed last February by a federal judge. The new offer involves a 
maximum of $120 million in cash for the roughly 130,000 investors in 
Prudential's Energy Income Funds. 
