<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN KLAIR IS CHOICE TO WIN EL ENCINO STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden Klair, who upset Pacific Squall and other older opponents in the Silver 
Belles Handicap last month at Hollywood Park, is the 3-1 favorite in today's 
$110,500 El Encino Stakes at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Never worse than third in her four American starts, Golden Klair earned her 
first U.S. victory by a half-length at 11-1 in the Silver Belles.Chris McCarron 
will again ride the daughter of Damister for trainer Darrell Vienna. 
</P>
<P>
 Stalcreek, who beat Golden Klair by a length in the Linda Vista Handicap over 
this track on Nov. 13, is the 7-2 second choice. She faded to fifth in the 
Dahlia Handicap on closing day of the Hollywood Park fall meeting, unable to 
handle a yielding turf course. With Eddie Delahoussaye serving the final day of 
his five-day suspension, Gary Stevens will ride Stalcreek. 
</P>
<P>
 The rest of the entrants for the 1 1/16-mile El Encino include Mamselle 
Bebette, Island Orchid, Vinista, Sensational Eyes, Alyshena, Tricky Princess 
and Supah Gem. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Rockamundo continued to prove his victory in last year's Arkansas Derby was a 
fluke by finishing last in his California debut Friday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 A 108-1 shot when he defeated Kissin Kris and eight others in the Arkansas 
Derby, Rockamundo has beaten 10 horses in five starts since. 
</P>
<P>
 Bossanova, the 5-2 second choice Friday, won the $50,000 allowance race, 
beating favored Tinners Way by nearly three lengths in 1:34 1/5 for the mile. 
BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
