<P>
OLLIE TAKES LAURELS IN NORTH HOLLYWOOD ROMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damon Ollie scored 31 points and grabbed 27 rebounds for North Hollywood High 
as the Huskies routed Canoga Park, 101-53, in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game 
Friday night at Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Ollie, with eight blocked shots, narrowly missed a triple double. 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood held a 45-24 halftime lead and ran off 32 points in the third 
quarter to put the game away. Fantasia Johnson had 21 points and 11 assists for 
the Huskies, who improved to 9-5 and 3-0 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
 Jody Edington scored 15 points for Canoga Park.  
</P>
<P>
 In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 57, Granada Hills 51 -- The visiting Golden Cougars trailed by 11 at 
halftime but played tough defense in the second half and limited the 
Highlanders to 15 points after intermission in the Northwest Valley game. 
Jelani Janisse had 25 points, 11 rebounds, two blocked shots and five of 
Kennedy's 11 steals. Steve Fisher led Granada Hills with 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft 63, El Camino Real 56 -- Lamont Magee had 19 points and Miles Blake added 
14 and eight rebounds coming off the bench to lead the host Toreadors (11-6, 
2-1) in the Northwest Valley Conference game. Magee hit five three-point 
baskets while Blake had four. 
</P>
<P>
 The Conquistadores' Charles Adams led all scorers with 25 points, 17 of which 
came in the first half. El Camino Real has yet to win a league game in three 
tries. 
</P>
<P>
 Poly 56, Van Nuys 26 -- Darrin Drew led all scorers with 17 points as the 
Parrots dominated defensively by holding the Wolves to two points in the first 
quarter and four in the third. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall 61, Verdugo Hills 56 -- Mike Sessions scored 14 points for the host 
Dons (4-8, 2-4) and Chan Cornish added 13 points and 13 rebounds in the 
Northern Conference loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Bryan DeLos Reyes also turned in a 13-point effort for Verdugo Hills, and 
David Bryant chipped in with 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock 58, Quartz Hill 43 -- The Rebels were held scoreless in the third 
quarter of the Golden League game. John George led Littlerock (7-8, 3-4) with 
15 points and Hassan Phillips added 11. Brad Deckstead led Quartz Hill with 13 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist 79, Marshall Fundamental 53 -- Landon LaPack scored 33 points, 
playing half the game, to lead the host Knights (12-3, 2-0) to an easy Alpha 
League victory. Craig Lord scored 15 points and Jeff Baumsteiger handed out 10 
assists for L.A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff 63, Calabasas 42 -- Ranger guard Mark Sebek scored 31 points, 
including 12 in the first quarter of the Frontier League game. He sank five 
three-pointers as Nordhoff improved to 5-10, 2-1. Freshman Ryan Coleman led the 
Coyotes with 15 points. 
</P>
