<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CSUN WINS THREE OF FOUR IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge men's volleyball team won three of four matches 
Friday on the opening day of the 30th UC Santa Barbara Invitational in Goleta. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors defeated Fresno State, 15-2, 15-3, and La Verne, 15-12, 15-8, but 
lost to Pepperdine, 15-9, 15-10 in group play, before defeating Hawaii, 15-7, 
15-10, in pool play. 
</P>
<P>
 WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Diana Cortez missed a triple double by one point to lead Cal Lutheran to a 
79-67 victory over Redlands for its first Southern California Intercollegiate 
Athletic Conference victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Cortez finished with nine points, 11 rebounds and 13 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Albert scored 17 points to lead Cal Lutheran (5-6, 1-1 in conference 
play). Redlands (5-6, 0-1) was led by Lisa Wewers with 16 points and 11 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Regals jumped to a 7-0 lead and led by two points at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran led by as many as 17 points in the second half as the Regals shot 
63% from the field after halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 In another women's basketball game: 
</P>
<P>
 Biola 73, The Master's 55 -- Rachel Schweiger scored 25 points to lead the 
Eagles in a nonconference game.  
</P>
<P>
 Master's (3-8) was led by Sharlene Tevelde with 16 points and Kim Douries with 
14. 
</P>
